The overall demographic composition of Marines and Sailors in the MRS has been reported.18-20,32 Overall, the analyses suggested that lower HRV at the predeployment visit, as measured by higher values of the LF:HF ratio, was associated with increased risk of a PTSD diagnosis at the postdeployment visit. Participants with high LF:HF ratios at the predeployment visit

